@startuml testing-pyramid-visual

title AI Trip Planner - Testing Pyramid Strategy

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor LightBlue
    BorderColor Black
}

package "Testing Strategy" {
  
  component "        E2E Tests (5%)        " as E2E #LightYellow [
    End-to-End Testing
    ----
    • Full user workflows
    • Browser automation  
    • Complete API flow
    • Slowest execution
    • Run before deploy
  ]
  
  component "                Integration Tests (15%)                " as Integration #LightGreen [
    Integration Testing
    ----
    • API endpoint tests
    • Service interactions
    • External API mocking
    • Database integration
    • Medium execution speed
  ]
  
  component "                                Unit Tests (80%)                                " as Unit #LightBlue [
    Unit Testing
    ----
    • Individual functions
    • Component isolation
    • Fast execution
    • High code coverage
    • Run on every commit
    • TDD friendly
  ]
  
}

E2E -[hidden]down-> Integration
Integration -[hidden]down-> Unit

note right of E2E
  **Execution Time:** 5-10 min
  **Cost:** High
  **Maintenance:** High
end note

note right of Integration
  **Execution Time:** 1-2 min
  **Cost:** Medium
  **Maintenance:** Medium
end note

note right of Unit
  **Execution Time:** 10-30 sec
  **Cost:** Low
  **Maintenance:** Low
end note

legend bottom left
  **Why Pyramid Shape?**
  • More unit tests = faster feedback
  • Fewer E2E tests = lower cost
  • Better test isolation at base
  • Optimal coverage/speed ratio
  
  **For AI Trip Planner:**
  • ~80 unit tests (agents, tools, services)
  • ~15 integration tests (API endpoints)
  • ~5 E2E tests (complete trip planning)
endlegend

note top
  **Total Tests: 100**
  Unit: 80 | Integration: 15 | E2E: 5
end note

@enduml
